language: East Sumbanese, Umbu Ratu Nggai dialect
Kadazan Dusun of Taginambur, Kota Belud, Sabah, Malaysia

annotation: 1)tau as in man, male. 2)tau as in one(person) one as in "the evil/bad one(tau tsikana)",  "the one who fights in a war/ a warrior(vetali tauna)", or in "the one who teaches/informs(veve?aripa tauna)" etc..
maru is commonly used to refer to man or male
Can also occur with inalienable possessor affixes when referring to a male child (kin)
Enfant male, de tout age; se dit aussi des animaux (Jnu)
PPn shows irregular loss of PCP ŋw.
also 'body': hau-?u = my body, au-?u = my feelings
